<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3471] Tests not working on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3471</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following tests are failing on Windows quite often:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SoftAutoCommitTest (all tests): There seem to be wrong assumes - I dont like the test &quot;testing&quot; how fast something is (there are slow machines or machines with &amp;lt;= 2 cores)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TestSolrDeletionPolicy1.testCommitAge() - also maybe timing issue. Otherwise I think the custom Solr DeletionPolicy is not respecting the fact that Windows cannot delete open files&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TestRealTimeGet.testStressRecovery(): See also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3461&quot; title=&quot;TestRealTimeGet.testStressRecovery() is sometimes very slow on Windows, using al CPUs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3461&quot;&gt;SOLR-3461&lt;/a&gt; for more discussion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I annotate the tests with an assume disabling Windows until this is fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
